  "text": "Generally, a decrease in branching intensity of any plant species corresponds to the tuning of growth to resource availability, at the whole-plant scale [CITATION_1] . In regions with dry winters, the usual drops of leaves of fourth-and fifth-order axes are expected as normal botanic events during the winter in coffee [CITATION_2] , which was expressed through their high terminal bud mortality, and high values of the phyllochron in this season.",
